Coleophora quercicola is a moth of the family Coleophoridae. It is found in Japan (Honshu) and South Korea.
The wingspan is 11–16.5 mm (0.43–0.65 in).The larvae feed on the leaves of Quercus mongolica. They create a blackish pistol-shaped case of about 8 mm (0.31 in) long. It is covered with yellowish-brown felt at the basal tubular part.